<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by kelson13:
[B]Actually, this spell reminds me a LOT of a low level Bard song.  There's a song where you target a mob and sing at it, then quickly target another mob and sing at it, etc.  You can only do it 2 or 3 times before the first song's duration runs out, so I wouldn't sing at more than 2 or 3 mobs before I pulled the remaining mob(s).

This spell seems to work the same way, but here's the kicker....if it's like the song, it's CHA based, and many Clerics simply don't have the CHA Bards and Enchanters do (My Bard used this song very well with 160 CHA).

So all you Dwarves who thought there wasn't really a downside to your race, this is it.  ;)  Nothing to lose sleep over, though.  I don't see why a Cleric would be the best puller your group can find anyway.  :P

It's a nifty spell, but if you don't have the CHA, it's useless.  My Cleric is Human and his CHA is 85.  Not that great, but I'd be willing to bet my success would be more than a Dwarven Cleric with this spell.

Eoin
Zeb[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
